<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3268: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moore</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-27T12:00:00-05:00">February 27,
                                1929—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>16. Your 21, February 26, 3 p.m. Telegraph us immediately when President
                            Leguia submits the report to Ambassador Figueroa. <pb facs="0865" n="729" xml:id="pg_729"/> I assume that it will be the same as your
                            19, February 21, 4 p.m. How is he going to get the proposition of
                            $3,500,000 before Ambassador Figueroa?</p>
                        <p>I am obliged to you for your prompt message.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>